Protesters in Makhanda, Eastern Cape are blocking roads leaving residents stranded yet again. Last month, residents and taxi operators shut down the town for three days to protest about the state of the roads and the lack of service delivery in the area. #DStv403 MAKHANDA - Protesters in Makhanda, Eastern Cape are blocking roads leaving residents stranded yet again. Last month, residents and taxi operators shut down the town for three days to protest about the state of the roads and the lack of service delivery in the area. READ: Makhanda residents beg for intervention Multiple schools and businesses have closed due to disruptions. Makana Municipality Mayor Mzukisi Mpahlwa says a lack of funds is causing a disruption in services.